  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (16b4ef6 2022-07-13T00:05:41.265337096Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n`forge init`\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n`forge init` produces a directory called `lib/forge-std`, which has two licenses present, `LICENSE-APACHE`, and `LICENSE-MIT`. It appears that the copyright holder is the same in both cases. This is mildly confusing.",
